Principal component analysis¶

In [9]:
pca = PCA()
pca_res = pca.fit_transform(data[numerical_features])
In [10]:
exp_var_pca = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
cum_sum_eigenvalues = np.cumsum(exp_var_pca)
In [11]:
plt.bar(range(0,len(exp_var_pca)), exp_var_pca, align='center', label='Explained variance')
plt.step(range(0,len(cum_sum_eigenvalues)), cum_sum_eigenvalues, where='mid',label='Cumulative explained variance')
plt.ylabel('Explained variance')
plt.xlabel('Principal component')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

TASK 2: Cluster analysis¶

In [16]:
color_depth = [64, 32, 16, 8, 4, 2]
In [17]:
image = Image.open("./capibara.jpg")
image = np.array(image, dtype=np.float64) / 255
w, h, d = original_shape = tuple(image.shape)
image_array = np.reshape(image, (w * h, d))
In [18]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(10, 6))
axes = axes.flatten()

for n_colors, ax in zip(color_depth, axes):
    image_array_sample = shuffle(image_array, random_state=0, n_samples=1_000)
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=n_colors, random_state=0).fit(image_array_sample)
    labels = kmeans.predict(image_array)
    ax.axis("off")
    ax.set_title(f"Quantized capibara ({n_colors} colors)")
    ax.imshow(kmeans.cluster_centers_[labels].reshape(w, h, -1))
    
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Clean messages¶

In [21]:
nltk_download('stopwords')
stop_words = stopwords.words("english")

def clean_text(text):
    text = text.lower()
    text = re.sub(r"@\S+", " ", text)
    text = re.sub(r"https*\S+", " ", text)
    text = re.sub(r"http*\S+", " ", text)
    text = re.sub(r"#\S+", " ", text)
    text = re.sub(r"\d", " ", text)
    text = re.sub(r'[%s]' % re.escape(string.punctuation), ' ', text)
    text = re.sub(r'\n', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub(r'\s{2,}',' ', text)
    text = text.replace('>', ' ')
    text = text.replace('<', ' ')
    text = text.replace('&lt', ' ')
    text = text.replace('&lt', ' ')
    text = text.replace('=', ' ')
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s]', '', text)
    text = ' '.join([word for word in text.split(' ') if word not in stop_words])
    return text

WordCloud¶

In [24]:
types = data['type'].unique()
for label in types:
    type_data = data[data['type'] == label]['message']
    text = ' '.join(type_data)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(text)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title(f'WordCloud for type: {label}')
    plt.show()

Vectorize texts¶

In [25]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(data['message'], data['type'], test_size=0.2, random_state=1337)
In [26]:
tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
X_train_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(X_train.values.tolist())
X_test_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.transform(X_test)

Classification¶

In [27]:
classifiers = {
    'Naive Bayes': MultinomialNB(),
    'AdaBoost': AdaBoostClassifier(),
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'k-NN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

for classifier_name, clf in classifiers.items():
    clf.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train)
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_tfidf)
    
    print(f"#################### {classifier_name} ####################")
    print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
    print("Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
